Given a TodoAction with a Scan covering all spec and marker IDs, the algorithm must produce todos by running computeEdgeTodos: a TodoEdgeDrift per baseline edge whose endpoint hash differs from baseline (with no covering resolution); TodoEdgeAdded and TodoEdgeRemoved for spec-spec edges appearing in only one of {baseline, scan}; TodoBrokenEdge for scan edges whose To endpoint does not exist; rhizomatic-closure TodoEdgeDrift for specs transitively reachable from a hash-drifted spec (with no covering resolution); and TodoCascade for markers linked to a chain-drifted spec. Edges with both endpoints unchanged must produce no todo. Edges with a matching resolution entry must produce no todo. When a node has been deleted (scan hash is empty string), the corresponding Deleted flag is set on the todo. The returned EvaluatedState propagates Edges and Resolutions unchanged. See principles.friction.